D.q[2858] = "To get out of here, you can either pay 2,000 Kamas of bail or wait 20 minutes. \nThis jail is way too small for us to lodge such wretched beings as you all the time...";
D.q[2862] = "You can now join our lines.\nWhich Order do you wish to join? \nThe warriors of the Bleeding Heart Order, the healers of the Unsound Mind Order, or the Putrid Eye Order?\nBe careful, this choice is very important. You won\'t be able to change your mind once you\'ve chosen your order.";
D.q[2863] = "You can now join our ranks.\nWhich Order do you wish to join? \nThe warriors of the Order of the Bleeding Heart, the healers of the Order of the Unsound Mind, or the Order of the Putrid Eye?\nBe careful, this choice is very important. You won\'t be able to change your mind once you\'ve chosen your order.";
D.q[2868] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[2870] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[2872] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[2884] = "To get out of here, you can either pay 128,000 Kamas of bail or wait one hour and twenty minutes. \nThis jail is way too small for us to lodge such wretched beings as you all the time...";
D.q[2890] = "Poochan thank you, poochan let you use some springs without danger, you just ask. You just give 2,000 Kamas to Poochan to clean the water after.";
D.q[2895] = "What a noble trade! A real Shield Smith puts his talent at the service of the weak. It\'s hard to take your opponents\' attacks if you don\'t have a shield. Anyway, don\'t forget that you\'ll be able to block these attacks only if you know your enemy perfectly well. A shield will be useless against monsters...\nBefore you can start your apprenticeship, you\'ll need the Shield Smith\'s hammer. Only a Hammer Smith will be able to provide you with this tool.";
D.q[2900] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try to come back in five hours, at least!";
D.q[2901] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try coming back in six hours, at least!";
D.q[2927] = "I see you know about the existence of elemental tonics... do you know also that only the greatest Pandawushu masters can use them? \nAs the Air Pandawushu master, I can provide you with my invigorating breath for your next fights...";
D.q[2933] = "I see you know about the existence of elemental tonics that only great Pandawushu masters can perform! \nAs the Earth Pandawushu master, I can make you become a real force of nature in your next few fights...";
D.q[2921] = "I\'ve some bad news. Some Bontarians have joined the ranks of Brakmar. There aren\'t any Renegade Hunters around right now, but if you bring me the hides of the Bontarian deserters, you can become a hunter yourself. I don\'t know where they are exactly, but a spy named Bishom Pot may be able to give you more information.";
D.q[2960] = "Oh my! You look pretty exhausted. If you go on like this my father will make short work of you. I\'d prefer it if that didn\'t happen because I always wanted to become Bworker instead of being Bworkie. \nTake these hairs and you\'ll be able to start from here once you\'ve recovered your strength.";
D.q[2961] = "You\'re back! I knew you weren\'t a coward. Give me back my hairs and I\'ll show you the way to the place where your strength abandoned you.";
D.q[2991] = "To add a new player in your friend list, click on his character and then on Add to my friend list";
D.q[2995] = "He copied one of my books and filled it with mistakes out of revenge... I know that his book is called Dragon Era. Copies of this book can be found in Astrub. I see... that you\'re dying to read this book, so just get me a copy!";
D.q[3020] = "I can\'t help you. OohoOohoOo I can feel that a spectre wants to talk to you through my mouth... You idiot, find god Xelor, it\'s not that hard! There you go! The message\'s been delivered!";
D.q[3022] = "Well done! You probably know that this sign is that of the infinite....OohoOo I can feel that a spectre wants to talk to you through my mouth....ohOho (in a lugubrious voice) Rotate this sign 90 degrees and you\'ll see a number. This number is the first coordinate of the place you need to go to. Change this number adding the sign minus in front of it and you\'ll get the second coordinate of the place you need to go to.";
D.q[3045] = "I hope that one day King Allister will deign let me visit his private apartments. Sigh.";
D.q[3061] = "With everything you\'ve brought us, we will be able to make our beautiful castle of which the whole world is already envious.";
D.q[3124] = "As for me... this is where I should be... in my den, with my Kaliptus leaves...and these adventurers... who come meet me... and have good times with me... But I digress... You probably came for... my Dofus... You silly old fool... I already explained it to you... It\'s Skeunk... and his Sadidettes... who stole it from me... They\'re hiding... in their hideout... close to the dark... dangerous... and smelly... valley... But...";
D.q[3125] = "But... you won\'t be able... to get in... without a key... I know... that Rigroulak has... one... and he\'s always... wanted... me to lend it... to him... my set... I\'m ready... to help you get... a part of it right now... and I\'ll give you... the other part... if you come back... and visit me...\nSee... I\'m a little bored... here...";
D.q[3134] = "Calm down first, and then I might calm down myself...\nI bet you\'d be interested in the key that opens Skeunk\'s hideout!\nThe horrible Eniripsa Master uses his four favourite Sadidettes to control the Koalaks!\nI\'ve no clue whatsoever about the type of magic they use, but it\'s very powerful. Almost all the koalaks on our mountains became aggressive and enslaved to these four sisters, who are loyal to this dreadful Skeunk!";
D.q[3135] = "Koalaks who resist this bewitchment are shut up in deep caves, or locked up in this primitive cemetery for eternity, and only those who have the gift of resurrection can escape...\nBut well, I\'ll be locked up in this gloomy place for the rest of my life and my ultimate wish is to look different to everyone else... I want to look like my idol, the Koolich. For this, I need his set... the complete set. Can you bring it back to me?";
D.q[3138] = "Halt! Who goes there?\nNo one enters the master\'s hideout without being invited or having a key. And I don\'t think that Master Skeunk and his disciples invited you. They would never invite villains and cheap adventurers like you into their hideout!\nBut maybe you have a key?";
D.q[3140] = "Did Rosal feed you some hallucinogenic flowers or what? \nTo be honest, I don\'t know how you can get permission since every time a crank like you asks me this question, I send them to the four sisters... and none have ever come back. All cowards.";
D.q[3150] = "Hello #1. I\'m Liroye Merline, Fidji Merline\'s sister and one of the most famous handywomen on the continent. My family has been doing things for itself for generations now, \'handying\' as we call it. Recently my sister and I decided to set up a business. Since we want to share what handiness we know with everyone, we\'ve decided to only open shops in enemy cities. Well, what handy hints do you want to know?";
D.q[3153] = "Here you go! With everything I\'ve taught you, you\'ll be able to create some basic items for breeders. But to do so, you\'ll need the appropriate tool - the Handyman Hammer. I don\'t have any to sell you. You\'ll have to find a hammer smith who has the time to make you one!";
D.q[3201] = "What are you doing here? \nYou\'re in the Labyrinth of the Minotoror, and just like all the other adventurers who came here before you, you\'ll get lost. I can sense it. Well, don\'t count on me to come get you out again! \nPfft. Anyway. What do you want?";
D.q[3213] = "How on earth did you manage to defeat the malodorous Minotot? \nWell, however you did it, it\'s time for you to get out of here. I have to tell you, by the way, you\'re quite the most boring person I\'ve ever met. \nFollow me. I\'ll take you back to the slab room.";
D.q[3212] = "The Minotoror is a terrible, legendary creature that can squash a Plucked Kirball under his hoofs! Rumour has it he eats Tofus and likes to throw them in his enemies\' faces. I fought the Minotoror when I was younger but I can\'t remember it... I was drunk and the only witnesses disappeared in this labyrinth forever. If you want to confront this terrible creature, you\'ll have to find relics: those of the Mumminotor and the Deminoball. These two creatures usually stroll in the rooms around this one, but be careful - they\'re even more bad-tempered than you!";
D.q[3221] = "Welcome to the slab room! Stand on one of these slabs and you\'ll be teleported into one of the rooms of this surprising maze, which is full of big Lousy Pigs. If you smell as bad as I think you do, you shouldn\'t feel too homesick!";
D.q[3226] = "What else? Right! Porcos Rustos are nomads. They bivouac and sleep under the stars until they find a place they like. Sometimes, they can even invade camps of adventurers if they feel like it.... As it happened in the south of Amakna...";
D.q[3230] = "What? You still want to continue this discussion? I\'ve already wasted enough time with you! Besides, I\'ve told you everything I know about the Porcos!";
D.q[3243] = "Indeed, they ended up losing control over this breeding. They could no longer tame the new generations of Dragons, Dreggons and Dragoss that they had created. No one can change the nature of such creatures, or really tame them... they\'re way too powerful and magic to be controlled by mere mortals. Further to several incidents, the Dragon breeder apprentices decided to give up their research on Dofus and they closed this sanctuary, locking up its occupants inside forever.";
D.q[3257] = "Well, this is no\' really an island... well it could be bu\', no.... It looks like some sort of gian\' floahing ice cube.\nBesides, the bloody ice cube\'s movin\' and the cap\'ain said we soon won\'t be able reach i\' any more....\n\n*sighs*\n\nWha\' a waste... It\'s a won\'erful place... There are treasures on the groun\', strange Treechnids.... A paradise for Enutrofs...";
D.q[3258] = "Yess... treasures on the ground... did the sun mel\' you\' brain o\' wha\'? \nStop repeatin\' everything like a bloody parrot... It\'s geh\'in on my nerves...\n\nI\'m goin\' back to my island while it\'s still there... So make up your mind... You comin\' or no\'?";
D.q[3271] = "Hello, my name is Josette. The famous Josette Moresyca... I was kidnapped and transformed into a Treechnid when I was only about 5 months old and then brought up by a family of Trunknids in the clearing of Liroye Merline. Ever since I was a little kid, I\'ve stood up for decent people who have been transformed into Treechnids and I\'m also looking for my roots. Is this a problem for you? Don\' t you like Treechnids? Well...\n\nWhat do you want to know?";
D.q[3287] = "What? You don\'t know this island? Well, I call it this way since that\'s where Otomai studies all the creatures of this world. \nI\'ve been stuck on this island for many years and instead of relaxing while sipping Kokoko juice cocktails on the beach, I decided to exploit my extraordinary talent as a creative handyman. \nHaven\'t I told you that I made and created a whole lot of different useful things yet?";
D.q[3294] = "Snirk!\nSquik snot snot gurlub squik?\nSquik snif kriss trok squik!";
D.q[3301] = "Haha! We are destined to rise to the top, like... like... whipped cream. Unlike whipped cream, however, we will be strong and firm. We will rule over mortals and gods alike with our new secret weapon. Even the dragons will be eating out of our hands!";
D.q[3320] = "I want to knoooock soooomeonnnne oooover! Bring me these Dragoturkeys! Quick!";
D.q[3327] = "The Koalak Mountain is a real paradise for us alchemists. I\'d like you to bring me back some flowers from this region. But beware of the protectors when you go, they\'re said to have the eyes of Sadida...";
D.q[3359] = "Warning! You\'ll need runes and items to run proper tests. Some colleagues of mine living in the area will have the runes and items you require. Are you ready to teleport to a workshop?";
D.q[3376] = "Yes! You have done well young one. I\'m impressed... but it\'s not over yet. Here is the key that will lead you to your next challenge.";
D.q[3379] = "I\'ve seen things you wouldn\'t believe... Huge ships on fire off the shoulder of Orion. I watched beams glitter in the dark near the Tanhauser Gate. All those ... moments will be lost in time, like tears ... in rain. Time to move on...";
D.q[3380] = "Arrrh, am sure I can fin\' ya somethin\' to do. Ther\' be\' a couple o\' places wher\' ya\'d need to take care o\' the rats. If the Master wants it done, it must be important. Here, start wi\' this.";
D.q[3421] = "Well, I think I\'ve told you everything I know about this rat and his history.\nBut be careful, this rat is driven by vengeance and he\'s training his turtles as well as other rats in the only goal to avenge his master. However, he seems to have lost his mind and he attacks anyone who dares enter his temple.\nTake care, he masters the Pandawushu art better than you can ever imagine.";
D.q[3422] = "How did you manage to defeat that rat? You should head over to Pandala Island and perfect your Pandawushu techniques, I\'d say you have incredible potential. \n \nAnyway, follow me, I\'ll get you out of this rat hole!";
D.q[3438] = "Hans told me he wanted to catch a Dragoturkey, yessir! He even told me he found a hut in the forest that no one but him knows about.";
D.q[3442] = "Oh man, I can be real stupid sometimes. But that doesn\'t change a thing. I\'ve locked up the kids... only I know where. If you do what I ask you, I might let the kids go. I really need to eat some good food. Find me a tasty dish to gobble or I\'ll eat the kids instead. ";
D.q[3459] = "Ahah! Yes, you seem to be heading South. If you come back round Astrub, will you tell me about your journey?";
D.q[3465] = "Me no want to become Trool mess...";
D.q[3479] = "Goblin tribe oppressed. Bworks want we in Workshop to make tapestry. If you spread Bwork blood, they forget we.";
D.q[3487] = "The Bworkdrift battle was very deadly. Eight days of wading through the blood of our comrades. There were more than 300 dead in my regiment alone. A sling ripped out the eyes of my best friend the Kaptain Bluebitt. My assistant Sergeant Uazindachit, suffered by my side for 3 days, both legs cut off by a Trool axe...";
D.q[3488] = "Our Bworklonel PlanBworksek had his stomach split open by a spell. It took guts to do what he did. I know, because I saw his assistant carry them off in a bowl afterwards. From time to time ... ah, ah, ah ... the brave goblin was knocking them over and the old goblin ... ah, ah, ah, was giving him a telling off.";
D.q[3489] = "That\'s a Bwork\'s routine. But, the most difficult thing was to eat Goblin to survive since our dead had already been eaten by our Trools. If you could make me dumb again, it would be nice. I\'ll give you PlanBworksek\'s fire Gobtrotter boots.";
D.q[3492] = "Me be paxifik. If you no agree, me hit you to explain!";
D.q[3508] = "I can\'t just abandon my tribe... do you know that people round here don\'t even talk to Bworks. We\'re lucky if they even touch us. I talked to Bworkid the paxifik but he\'s very touchy and that KrazyBwork only dwells on his old battles.";
D.q[3511] = "To start: Goblin skin, Sadida hair tuft and Trool bones. Here\'s a scalpel. With it, you\'ll be able to bone a Trool. Try the nearest dungeon or the pit.";
D.q[3526] = "Bring Troofle, Fattrool, the red cape and Litol will follow you. Guide him to Bworknroll.";
D.q[3528] = "Oldest child, Gobincarnat become first goblin magus. Give Troofle, Fattrool, a red cape and my Litol to Bworknroll. He lives in rat larder.";
D.q[3537] = "Ah an Eniripsa disciple! I\'m happy to see that some still choose the difficult path of healing. Your strength is not in harassing and slaughtering your enemies... You\'re no ordinary warrior, child, so your task is no ordinary one. Good luck to you. The path you have chosen will lead you to glory.";
D.q[3563] = "Be nice! If me no have gift, female no happy because say me not real chief.";
D.q[3585] = "Thanks. Me stay here anyway. Great mage Bworknroll give Trool tamed to me. Goblin stop throw stones!";
D.q[3587] = "Me call friend Trool!";
D.q[3617] = "My heart vibrates, vibrates, vibrates.";
D.q[3634] = "You must persist, I know you can do it. If you need a weapon, go and see Telma Faker. She\'s not too far from here, a little to the south... and she always has plenty to trade.";
D.q[3637] = "You again! I like you, you little larva. Come over to my house, you can have tea some time! If you do as I say, one day you won\'t be a larva anymore... you\'ll be a minister of war...";
D.q[3652] = "I know what you mean, there\'s nothing worse than people who\'ve got nothing better to do but stand around talking all day. Some folk just talk and talk and talk. What were we saying? Ah yes. Go talk to my cousin Postor Nhin, you never know, he might have something for you to do.";
D.q[3661] = "Great! Here\'s the parcel. Take it to Xelorat Masket. If you know how to use the Zaaps, you should use one to reach her.";
D.q[3702] = "Your axe cannot cut that Elm. In between naps, the god Sadida noticed that too many people were exploiting the plants of our World. Since then, he appointed tree, flower and cereal protectors.";
D.q[3728] = "Danaida read the book of truth but she has forgotten much. The book is rare even in Amakna. She will tell you what she can of Iop\'s victory.";
D.q[3730] = "Laura told you about the book? I read it when I was down in Amakna... what I told Laura is only bits and pieces of the original. One day, you might be lucky enough to come across the book yourself... if you do, be sure and take in all you can!";
D.q[3749] = "You need a lot of wood to make a proper plank. You must find at least twenty units of Ash wood. When you put them on the workbench, the end result of your work will be there for you to see. If this is the case, then normally, everything should be fine. Sometimes, the wood will fail, things will go wrong and you\'ll lose everything. Well, swallow your pride and try again! If you can\'t see anything on the wood panel, it\'s because you either put in too much or not enough wood.";
D.q[3787] = "Ahh, you remind me of me when I was your age... Now, concentrate, I\'m gonna put a tiny little spell on you. You won\'t feel a thing... after a while.";
D.q[3790] = "I\'ll give you a Twiggy Sword for eight wood logs. For four measures of wheat, I\'ll give you a loaf of hot bread from Amakna. For five flax flowers, how about a potion of mini healings. Have you got a gudgeon? I\'ll take the guts for my Bow Meow and you can have the rest. I\'ve got a lot of things, stranger. Show me what you got and maybe we can do a deal!";
D.q[3803] = "That\'s for me to know, you to find out. You think I got this far without some hidden talents? How about I give you this rare object for it?";
D.q[3817] = "Incarnam Lemonade! Hem, yes, give it to me. It\'s ... mmmm ... essential for my concentration. OKAY. Now for the real magic... I\'m going to give you all your strength back. By the way, young adventurer, take care of yourself, nothing is the same in Amakna. If you want to replenish your energy over there, you\'ll have to find an Inn to rest at... or potions that will restore your energy. I always go for the Incarnam Lemonade myself!";
D.q[3822] = "This stupid telescope still isn\'t working. Even though I whip Biltinix every morning, he never has time to come help me. Maybe I should ask Xelorat Masket, but she\'s already very busy fixing Zaaps. One day, it will work, and on that day you\'ll be able to see the entire world through its lens.";
D.q[3832] = "I\'m a true-a arrtist. I\'m-a drrawing da village under me. It\'s-a my work, my life. But I need da gouache to esprress-a my taaalent!... You too! Esprress your-a talent. Go get me the coloours of envy...";
D.q[3853] = "Hey, kid, that\'s life. I had some great times and I\'ve no regrets. It\'s the journey that counts, right? All the long days and nights I spent looking for one of those eggs... I discovered more countries than I can count, creatures as strange as a three Kama piece... some great brothers in arms, too. Hey, look, enjoy your trip round the World of Twelve... and take care.";
D.q[3877] = "Eh, er, what? Whoaa I was having such a sweet dream... Okay, tell me what you found. Oh no, there\'s nothing in those crypts... Listen, there\'s a crypt south of here... The gate seems blocked, but if you try, perhaps...";
D.q[3893] = "Come back later, I\'m thinking about my next plan.";
D.q[3895] = "So, you want to prove your value... Go attack a neutral character... don\'t hesitate to ask for help, they\'re well protected...";
D.q[3900] = "Well, good choice... Don\'t forget to show your scroll of recommendation so that my other friends know who you are. For now, you\'re on trial and you\'ll have to prove your loyalty to our cause. Ask Vil Smisse what he expects from his Rogues...";
D.q[3933] = "Haa what?... No, I was thinking about my next wonderful creation for the King... Hurry up and bring me those strings. I need them soon!";
D.q[3934] = "Thank you! You see, I\'ll use this silk to make a wedding dress for Allisteria, the King\'s niece! I can feel it already... it\'s gonna be a masterpiece!";
D.q[3935] = "Yes, I brought a lot of cawwots from the island... It seems a Wabbit prince is on his way to Amakna.";
D.q[3960] = "A force-feeding potion? Lucky you! I\'ve just invented one! You\'ll be the first one to test it!";
D.q[3963] = "That\'s good, you\'ve got what I asked you... However, we will not be able to use it as the prince employs a taster. Bring me enough Kamas to hire a team of assassins.";
D.q[3966] = "The assassins I found will not be able to get through the security that surrounds the prince. Find a Lenald. With your skill and his magic, he may be able to teleport you to the throne room on day of the wedding.";
D.q[4000] = "Interesting, how will you do that?";
D.q[4009] = "Oh, poor me! My master threw me out into the street! Me...such a good servant!";
D.q[4019] = "Oh, you\'we back nice squiwe! I wanted to ask...";
D.q[4021] = "The Tofu attack failed... I must come up with a new plan.";
D.q[4094] = "Hans told me he wanted to catch a Dragoturkey, yessir! He even told me he found a hut in the forest that no one but him knows about.";
D.q[4103] = "You have all the necessary ingredients but what\'s more important to me is that you helped my friends and I thank you for that. Now, it\'s my turn to help you.\nBy changing your constitution, your characteristics will also be modified. \nYour chance, strength, intelligence, wisdom, vitality and agility can therefore be modified.\nI can suggest two different potions that will enable you to change your constitution. The first one will enable you to totally forget your characteristics, whereas the second one is less powerful. \nBe careful, once you drink one of these potions you can\'t go back, unless you drink another potion again.";
D.q[4104] = "I\'m sorry but I can\'t make you a potion to change your constitution, you don\'t have the right ingredients for it. These potions are so powerful that they require extremely rare magic essences. The more powerful the persons who must change their constitution are, the more I need ingredients.\nPreparing these potions is quite a long and delicate process and I only prepare them for adventurers who are taking the time to go and help my colleagues on this island.";
D.q[4107] = "What? You want more Dizbi essence? Here, this is one of my last flasks, use it wisely.";
D.q[4109] = "Howdy ho adventurer! \nI\'m Ma Lee Key, mother of all DIY Key Makers! \nSay what? You didn\'t know there\'s handy folk what make their own keys?\nWell aren\'t you dumb. Why\'d you come down to these parts if you\'re so stoopid, huh?";
D.q[4124] = "Do you really think that you just need to accept my proposition to go on this island? You fool of the ocean depths, stupid centenarian Kralove dung!!! If you go to this island you\'ll live a dangerous adventure! You\'ll have to fight the elements, the oceans and maybe even your aunts! Hehehe... I\'ve always enjoyed making rhymes! \nDo you really want to go on this island or would you rather keep hunting Gobblies?";
D.q[4139] = "I knew you didn\'t have much to do at the moment! \nSo, the job I\'m offering you is quite simple. I need to heal the Coralators that are walking on the beach. Some strange parasitic molluscs are slowly eating their brains... The only thing that we can do to save them is to give them a Bulbish potion, strong enough to heal the most advanced cerebral wounds. When you get a chance, you should try this potion, it would do you good!!! Anyway... Try to find a competent alchemist and bring me back this potion as soon as you can.";
D.q[4144] = "I never build breeding machines myself. I usually modify the machines that handymen make for breeding Dragoturkeys. It\'s not the best solution but it works pretty well. I\'d like you to bring me an ash slapper, an ash drinking trough, an ash lightning thrower, an ash manger and an ash plank. I\'ll then dismantle, modify and adapt them to my own creatures.";
D.q[4157] = "I\'ve hidden here because I could no longer stand my dad. He keeps on calling me my wabbit... can you imagine the torture? It\'s been hard enough already to accept my name as it\'s... I never liked my name Bugsbo Nee and besides all this, he keeps on making a fool of me in front of all my girlfriends with this stupid nickname. I\'ll never have a serious relationship!!! \nIf only my dad could understand this, I think that I\'d consider seeing him again.\nCan you try and explain to him what\'s bothering me?";
D.q[4174] = "Hello! I\'m Flip Flap, like the noise from a Scaraleaf\'s wings... Isn\'t that a funny name for a Scarplane pilot? Scarplanes are tamed Scaraleaves which have been trained to fly long distances. We sometimes add wooden wings and wheels for landing.";
D.q[4177] = "Finally! I think I\'ll use my ginger mount on even days and my almond mount on odd days. A dream come true!";
D.q[4183] = "Hello! I\'m the famous Kito. My family has been flying Scarplanes for twelve generations... we\'re still not perfect, but hey...\nFor instance, my cousin became a Zaapi Cleaner, and my nephew became a Dragoturkey breeder. Whatever...";
D.q[4186] = "I\'ve heard that you managed to scare the Pirates away. They\'ll probably leave me alone for a while with their cannonballs!\nAll Scarplane pilots will be grateful to you!!!";
D.q[4189] = "Incredible! You defeated the Black and Pink Knight. I\'ve dreamt of this so many times... Unfortunately I never was strong enough to succeed.\nTo thank you, you can use my Scarplane to go wherever you want.";
D.q[4199] = "Since we can\'t intervene in the evolution of the island species, we\'re doing our best to control and understand their evolution. But things have changed since. The Tynril seems to have become the King of the Dark Jungle. Nothing can stop him and it seems that he\'s becoming crazier and crazier. Since he\'s the master of this own territory, the Tynril is no longer interested in breeding and making his species evolve, and I must admit that it worries me. I think that if you could defeat him, he would recover his former interest and might start making his offspring evolve again.";
D.q[4215] = "Warning! With this potion all of your characteristics will be reset. \nYou\'ll lose all of the characteristic points that you gained through scrolling.\nOnce you\'ve reset, you\'ll be able to distribute your characteristic points again. \nDo you really want to continue?";
D.q[4217] = "When I arrived, I noticed that the island used to be inhabited. By who? \nI don\'t know.\nBut the civilization that used to live on this island had already built buildings, and alchemy labs. \nWe only restored what was there already. Besides, from time to time we even find some new labs buried in this island.";
D.q[4273] = "If it\'s an important citizen you\'re looking for and he hasn\'t been in my inn, you should try the Atyu Sirvis\' Inn. Why exactly are you looking for this person by the way?";
D.q[4275] = "Sometimes important people pass through the North, near Ufot\'s house. I\'ve heard customers talking about it, but never heard them mention Xephires\' name.";
D.q[4304] = "Oh him? It\'s a Pandawa... a master in the art of pandawushu. He could tear out one of your toenails from 10 yards away and you wouldn\'t know a thing until you took your shoes off. You should go see him in action, it\'s quite impressive! Not as impressive as me of course... but what is?! If you\'re thinking of going to look for him, you\'ll need all the luck you can get... he\'s just gone on a pilgrimage to the Agony V\'Helley.";
D.q[4306] = "My colleagues assisted me for many years in my researches, I\'d never have discovered so many things without them. I feel like I owe them something and I\'m glad that for my potions other adventurers can help them. \nI\'d like you to help the Professor Kalkulus, Stella Stukup, Polka Merer, Kito, the Doctor Nauh, Speet Fyer, and Flip Flap.";
D.q[4310] = "I haven\'t seen you in a long while. I thought the Giant Kralove had swallowed you whole. Don\'t forget to go have a drink with the other militiamen from time to time. I hate nothing more than a fool who thinks about work all the time.";
D.q[4314] = "We don\'t have a moment to lose. Some dodgy people have found out about the Milone Jewel and a trustworthy source told me that the robbers were on the point of going to steal it. Go to Milone\'s place quickly with this letter and stop them taking the jewel.\nIf you cross any militiamen on the way, take them with you.";
D.q[4317] = "Who do you take me for? Hmm, now that I think about it, it wouldn\'t do any harm to buy a Crimson Claw.\nYou\'re in luck. That cretin Grimpil is only in town for a while. I saw him make for Bagrutte\'s Inn, but he\'s avoiding me like the plague, and he\'s dead right too. If he so much as looks at me, he\'ll get a taste of my Claw of Ceangal.";
D.q[4335] = "Hahaha! I knew that he couldn\'t refuse an offer like that. We\'ve gained an important ally in the battle against Bonta. You\'ve done well, you little worm, but give me back my jewel.";
D.q[4348] = "As you can see, there are signs of a battle in this corner. What happened? Well I found this weapon on the ground too. \nOh, you\'re doing an investigation, well here\'s the weapon, maybe it\'ll come in useful. Kosuke the smith will be able to tell you where it comes from, but surely you\'ve thought of that already.";
D.q[4351] = "If the Ecaflip is a traveller, he probably stopped in one of the city\'s inns. Go ask the tavern keepers if they\'ve seen any Ecaflips lately, and don\'t hang around boozing, remember you have a job to do.";
D.q[4353] = "A crime scene and an Ecaflip\'s sword you say? We\'ll have to continue investigating then. You\'re doing a great job, keep it up.";
D.q[4360] = "News? Did the tavern keepers know something?";
D.q[4365] = "Hmm, so you found the bandits and you even went as far as risking you life to get into their hideout. I admire your courage, but I need people with sense too. It\'s a pity you didn\'t get any further into their hideout. \nI wanted to raise a troop to go along with you, but the counsel didn\'t agree with me. With the new information you brought me I hope they\'ll change their minds.";
D.q[4368] = "I want you to make preparations to leave. You can expect combat. The convoy is waiting for at the south gate, but I couldn\'t find any more militiamen to accompany you since I needed all the men I could find for missions around the town. The public paddocks were opened during the night by some troublemakers and there are Dragoturkeys running amuck all over the city. It really is a mess. Go see Cheeka the convoy leader real quick, and don\'t forget to report back to me as soon as the convoy arrives safely.";
D.q[4374] = "Let\'s hope the valuable jewel will attract the leader of the bandits and that we\'ll be able to capture him. We also made sure that the news spread quick, so they\'re bound to find out. Could you go collect the jewel at Marge the jeweller\'s place, please. You\'re the only person I trust for this kind of business.";
D.q[4390] = "I\'ve been thinking a lot and I\'ve come to an important decision. I\'m going to cover you so you can continue your investigation and find out once and for all who betrayed Bonta. We can keep an eye on you when you\'re around the town, but it\'s not so easy when you stray outside. Go to the Sram temple and question Rigal Hookhand. I\'m not fond of the guy, but he may have some useful information all the same. Let\'s just hope he does!";
D.q[4391] = "Come closer, don\'t be frightened. The shadows may hide your face, but they cannot hide your soul. What Rigal does not know, he learns soon enough. Why did you come, child... why?";
D.q[4394] = "Let\'s see... X... Xena the Shoemaker, Xav the... no... Xiron... I don\'t recognise any of these names. Ah, here it is! Xarthan! He\'s well known around Bonta and I think he must be your man. I can\'t see any other Bontarians on this list.";
D.q[4397] = "Time to close the trap. Go to the Tower of Bonta. Many important citizens of the city are meeting there soon and you\'re going to take this chance to get into Xarthan\'s house. Find the documents that compromise him - when you have the documents you\'ll know what to do next. I don\'t want him finding out that you were there, so you\'ll need to take a handyman with you to force the lock discreetly.\nXarthan\'s house is in the Baker\'s district in Bonta. Where exactly? I don\'t have a clue, the sod never even invited me once! \nMay Silvosse bring you luck!";
D.q[4414] = "I didn\'t think the two of you would get beaten, but I sent some guards there and they took him out at the Tower door. \nYour help an determination have been very valuable to us. Bonta owes you big for having unmasked the traitor. Him and his accomplice will be questioned and I\'ll make sure that Xephires\' riches are distributed among the common people.";
D.q[4431] = "According to Mulic Bere\'s report, no self-respecting smith would put his name to the equipment in the Bontarian Militia. He doesn\'t think that Kosuke Ichazum, Bonta\'s blacksmith, is responsible for such mediocre work but he wants assuring before getting him involved. For the time being, collect 5 Hurrian Hammers and swap them for the blacksmith\'s tools. When you\'ve done that, come back and see me.";
D.q[4438] = "We can\'t allow this ridiculous behaviour here. The Way of Djaul is the only true Brakmarian creed. I am satisfied with what you have done.";
D.q[4471] = "In the depths of a cave to the south-west, in the Porcos Territory. I must warn you that he\'s a little odd and fairly paranoid. I\'m not quite sure if he\'ll agree to talk to you. \nBut enough about that... who are you? And why are you asking me this?";
D.q[4497] = "Why am I not surprised... The quality of this weapon leaves a lot to be desired. So now we\'ve an incompetent smith and an attendant who refuses to believe it. We\'ll have to find another solution to our problem, and I already have an idea what to do.";
D.q[4498] = "Hmm, Bonta is having trouble and you need a smith?\nI can\'t take care of it, but maybe...\nNo, forget about it.";
D.q[4502] = "It\'s not Kamas we need... it\'s just that this Latem Sa smith is really incompetent and as Kosuke Ichazum is a specialist in blades, he can\'t make a standard set for our militia. I want you to find a mercenary smith who\'ll agree to work for us. Start by asking Kosuke Ichazum if he knows anyone who could help.";
D.q[4508] = "I\'ve already dealt with them...\nIf they win the conflict, they\'ll chase me from my mine and will surely force me to work for them. I\'d rather die! All the same, I don\'t trust you any more than them. Trust is earned, so you\'ll have to prove to me that you\'re worthy.";
D.q[4510] = "Hello, how are you getting on with Nara? Is he as competent as they say?";
D.q[4513] = "I can\'t work here, I just can\'t bear hearing those cries of agony every time the Moowolf sits down to eat. I need a quieter place, where less people pass by. every time I hear footsteps I\'m afraid someone has come to get me. Who would want to hurt me? Well... lots of people. Smiths who are jealous of my skill, or thieves, or even the ghosts of monsters out for revenge...";
D.q[4514] = "Do you remember William Lenglad, the young troublemaker you roughed up not so long ago? Well, you\'ll have to go talk to him again, he\'s got a new sidekick. An idiotic old Bwork, but an old Bwork who seems quite dangerous all the same.\n... Go teach them another lesson! And make sure they don\'t forget it this time!";
D.q[4516] = "If you, like me, have seen enough of the segregation that\'s tearing this town apart, the rich on the left and poor on the right and...\nAAAH! It\'s you! Let me warn you: my new partner \'Bawurk\', as he calls himself, will give you what\'s coming to you and that\'ll be the last I\'ll see of you.";
D.q[4518] = "Wow, you really got stuck in! Still, at least it\'ll keep him quiet for a while. Thanks to you, the town\'s businessmen and women can get back to work and will stop moaning about the militia, allowing us to get down to more important things. Justfa Lafs isn\'t happy with our military tactics. He said they left a lot to be desired! As head of the militia, I\'m obliged to make sure my men are being trained properly. Go see Justfa Lafs and ask him if he can think of any way to improve our troops\' performance in the field.";
D.q[4530] = "That\'s a very good question. We already have lots of works about magic and many spellbooks. I really don\'t see what you\'re going to bring to our arsenal, except a bit of demonic or Bwork magic.";
D.q[4536] = "Bishom Pot reported some very troubling news. Brakmar seems to have realised that our equipment is weak, and they\'re preparing a huge attack! \nWe\'ve started equipping our militia with better items thanks to Nara, but you\'ll need to get into the Tower of Brakmar to see if you can gather any more information about their plan.";
D.q[4550] = "Ahh, so that\'s why Danathor wanted to speak with you...     Thanks for telling me, but alas, it\'s useless. Your testimony is worthless considering the support he has from his high-placed friends. The best thing to do is to find the thief he hired.";
D.q[4548] = "So, our efforts were not in vain. At present, we have a better militia and with a bit of luck, we\'ll come out of this without so much as an injured soldier. With this letter in our possession, we\'ll certainly be able to condemn Xephires and he won\'t even be able to use his relatives to slow the process down. \nYou\'ve done a great job, as usual. Bonta owes you much and instead of giving you a shield, which you may not use, I\'m going to reward you with everything you need to make one. Or you pick a weapon, and I\'ll give you everything you need to make one of those. \nThings are looking very peaceful around here for the moment, so this is your chance to go and see the masters of the order.";
D.q[4552] = "The Lenalds lived on what is now Wabbit Island. They were pacifists and could not resist the invading Wabbits who used all kinds of strategies to exterminate them and steal their lands. Only a handful of Lenalds survived the massacre and they still live to the south of the island.";
D.q[4555] = "I\'d love to help you, but if I do I\'ll need a favour in return. If you can bring me one of my manuals I\'ll help you make this bandana ship-shape again.";
D.q[4570] = "Dangerous this island is. Leave you must. Or maybe information from me you seek?";
D.q[4578] = "Haak taak. Purr vrut!";
D.q[4569] = "The guardian really exists, but he\'s refusing to co-operate? I hope you weren\'t sharp with him, it\'s totally out of the question to use Brakmarian methods. As soon as you\'ve recovered from your journey, I\'ll have another mission for you. Hurry up and get better.";
D.q[4609] = "We can\'t take the bandana to Elturt in that state. Ask the best tailors in Bonta, Brakmar and Astrub if necessary to fix it up for you.";
D.q[4625] = "The horn should be on Moon Island and you have taken the trouble to prepare some Kokonuts for your next mission? Excellent initiative. If only the other militiamen showed such foresight, Bonta would have fallen a long time ago.";
D.q[4629] = "You almost found out where the horn was and you let a... a turtle scare you off? \nGo back there and pull some information out of it at any cost!\nThreats... violence... do what you must!";
D.q[4637] = "Listen up and listen well: you\'re as incapable and as useless as a Plain Pikoko in the middle of the Asse Sea. As punishment for your incompetence, I want you to bring me an Army of Plain Boar Ticks. It will remind you how insignificant you\'re and just how much I hate failure.";
D.q[4639] = "So, you Trool Dung Beetle turd, are you happy with your new mission?";
D.q[4644] = "What are you waiting for? Bonta cannot get hold of those documents!";
D.q[4650] = "Do you want to get caught too? Go back to that dog Oto and give me some peace!";
D.q[4662] = "You have followed the recipe to the letter? You didn\'t add any personal touches? In any case, we\'ll have to settle for that, we don\'t have time to prepare a second one. Have you got any Longevity Potion left, by chance?";
D.q[4667] = "What? Did I really just hear what I think I heard? You stupid idiot! You stinking piece of Ouassingue turd!\nGet out of my sight before I kill you!";
D.q[4672] = "At the moment, I\'ve something else I\'d like you to do. A Sram owes me some money, and it\'s already been two months since I asked her to pay me back. She must be skint, so find her, and eliminate her. Don\'t let her hoodwink you, she\'s a real smooth talker - if you listen to a word she says, you\'ll end up skint yourself. Believe me, I know what I\'m talking about. I know exactly what you\'re thinking, and you\'d be wrong. She didn\'t hoodwink me, oh no. She owes me money for something else. I\'m too clever for her, do you hear? She loves to gamble, you\'ll find her if you ferret around in the illegal gaming rooms.";
D.q[4745] = "Hello *hic*, how are you? I\'m Bonta\'s judge and *hic* I would love to help you out, but I\'m very busy at the moment. If the matter isn\'t extremely *hic* urgent, please speak to one of the three clerks. I hope that doesn\'t bother you. *hic*\nGoodbye.";
D.q[4694] = "Sorry to bother you with this, but a friend of mine, a militiaman called Kit Dingaround, is under suspicion of having betrayed Bonta for a bribe... that\'s why he was thrown in jail like a common criminal. He\'s a great kid and would never even think of doing such a thing. I\'m convinced that it\'s a plot against him! Go see Kit in prison and try to clear the story up.";
D.q[4746] = "A delay in the treason case? Hmm, hmmm... *hic*\nI hate investigations that drag on, but since you seem like a decent chap, I\'ll do what you *hic* ask in exchange for a little favour from you.\nI need alcohol to make the prisoners talk but the reserves have run out. *hic* I need a barrel of Shambrosia to continue with the questioning, only Gordo McRamsay in Amakna knows the secret. Oh, and while you\'re here, I\'m looking for an Astrub woman too, but marriage agencies aren\'t what they used to be. It would be great if you could handle it instead.";
D.q[4827] = "I was appointed clerk because my Order is neutral in this conflict. Talk about luck...*Yawns*";
D.q[4877] = "Hello, I have already sent militiamen to monitor the sewer entrance but Gnirreh has not reappeared. Go down into the sewers yourself, through the south-east entrance, and have a look around. There\'s already a militiaman there handling the most southerly part, so once you\'re in the sewers, head west.\nIf you manage to find Gnirreh, bring him here, willingly or unwillingly. The future of a Bontarian militiaman depends on his testimony.";
D.q[4969] = "I was told of the existence of a certain symbol which is currently in the possession of the Dreggons. As luck would have it, I need one just like theirs for the temple. I have thought of a way for you to get it. You\'re going to disguise yourself as a Dreggon and just ask them for it! Well, what are you waiting for?!";
D.q[5033] = "(The symbol on the safe is of a Tofu. Since As\'Ruoy\'Dnim could not even begin to understand the concept of humour, the likelihood that he is impressed by the symbol is much closer to zero than any other figure you could think of...)";
D.q[5253] = "Well, was Divad able to identify the guilty party?";
D.q[5254] = "JIVA?!\nHow dare she!? Djaul will know of this mascarade!";
D.q[5132] = "The Bantam Potion failed, but it doesn\'t matter. When I saw that whale, I said to myself I wasn\'t so fat after all.";
D.q[5403] = "Come on now, sing with me. \'It\'s my friend, Bibi. What a great Blop, I call him on the Blopophone to see if he\'s at home. He always helps me out...\'\nDon\'t you want to sing with me?\nWell, which room do you want to go to?";
D.q[5471] = "Hello, I\'m Dolce Geurrara, the famous mycologist, and brawler in my spare time. I snatched what I could of the Pandawushu style and set up my own martial arts school, based on decapitating fungi. Without hands, if you please! \nWell let\'s get down to business. What do you want to know?";
D.q[5521] = "Ok, let\'s see now... Stable situation over the last fourteen days... hmmm... The Amakna social services can help you alright. \nYou can become an Amaknan once more, but you\'ll lose your rank in the militia... and all the advantages that come with it.\nThe administrative costs can be very high according to your reputation and your achievements, so think long and hard before you decide. \nDon\'t forget! You have to go through each step in the procedure if you want to become Neutral. If you quit before completing the process, you\'ll lose any money you\'ve spent.";
D.q[5523] = "If serving Bonta is your bag, I can arrange the papers to affiliate you to their militia. That\'ll save me some time and it won\'t cost you a penny. \nWhy am I doing all this, you ask. Well, Bonta gives me a few perks for every new recruit I send their way. \nHowever, I suggest you go see Snori Nairb in Astrub before you join the alignment, he rewards anyone who wishes to enrol.";
D.q[5535] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the God Enutrof has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5536] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the God Sram has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5544] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Pandawa has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5558] = "So, to sum up - I\'ll send two Tofus into the workshop while Merlinmagus Ambrosius has his back turned. The fist Tofu will eat some Poppy Seeds and the second will replace them with Scurvion seed. If I\'m seen I\'ll just summon a Crackler and run for it. If everything goes according to plan, Bonta\'s entire food supply will be poisoned. Does that sound good?";
D.q[5562] = "Hey, it\'s too late. A militiaman just left with the recipe. For once I got it right first time.... But if you get there quick, maybe you can take it back. Show me your map, I\'ll mark where you have to go.";
D.q[5566] = "At the moment I\'m a militiaman in the Bontarian forces, but I\'m going to convert to the other side and open a high-calorie restaurant chain. I just have to find some Trool hunters to get the meat for me and some fishermen to catch the fish and chips.";
D.q[5568] = "It\'s a pity you arrived so late. Well, I suppose it\'s not really your fault. All the same, I want you to keep these modified cereals for yourself. And don\'t let the cat out of the bag. If the citizens find out, we\'ll have a riot on our hands. \nBy the way, how did it go with Fidji Merline?";
D.q[5574] = "Very good. I\'m delighted you\'ve become an apprentice of mine. \nForced resurrection takes a long time to get right, so I won\'t be needing you for the time being. Go keep an eye on your companions, just as the goddess Jiva keeps an eye on you!";
D.q[5578] = "You dare to threaten me? You\'d be better off getting out of here before the Astrub mercenaries find you, dirty scoundrel.";
D.q[5579] = "How dare you insult me. I\'m not begging... not like those bums at Astrub bank.";
D.q[5583] = "You managed to convince him? Not too bad at all. But while you were off playing tourist in Astrub, Bonta found a way to raise its cereal production.\nBring me 20 Scurvion seeds, and this time, you\'d better hurry. If not, you\'ll be getting a week of intensive training, and you don\'t want that.";
D.q[5588] = "Hey, come on, who do you think you\'re? Have some respect for your elders, you little Gobball pat. Your mother mustn\'t have given you enough spankings when you were a child, but don\'t worry, I\'ll bring it up to date once I get my body back.";
D.q[5603] = "This idiot Merlanmagus will find nothing there but fire. As for you, you\'re now officially a Dark Spy. \nSo? Happy?";
D.q[5613] = "Old Terroh Cogitoh would reolly like a hond, but I hove to go see the Enutrofs first.";
D.q[5625] = "Hey, listen, you couldn\'t spare a few Kamas by any chance, could you? I just need to get into my bank. I\'m the richest Eniripsa in Astrub, but I left all my wealth in the bank, so I can\'t get to it.";
D.q[5621] = "Hmm, I see. They\'re not leaving me with any choice. They don\'t want to admit anything, we\'ll have to bring out the big guns. \nYou\'re going to go to Astrub and convince Deni Hoobe to come to Bonta. By any means necessary except violence.";
D.q[5638] = "You know what? I\'ve excellent telepathic powers. I can project my thoughts around me, and it seems as if I was talking normally, except that the sound is only in the peoples\' heads. I can prove it if you don\'t believe me. Watch this...\n*Thinks* I\'ll buy every drop of Vampire blood you have, 1 Kama per unit. I\'ll buy it all.\n*Thinks* I\'ll buy every drop of Vampire blood you have, 1 Kama per unit. I\'ll buy it all.\n*Thinks* I\'ll buy every drop of Vampire blood you have, 1 Kama per unit. I\'ll buy it all.\n*Thinks* I\'ll buy every drop of Vampire blood you have, 1 Kama per unit. I\'ll buy it all.\nSee, it works perfectly.";
D.q[5649] = "The ritual of Erzal\'s Curse has finally come good and Terra Bitya has been resuscitated. Go see her and question her until she tells you where to find those statues. Do whatever you think is necessary.";
D.q[5656] = "Haha, I see. You\'ve got a devious mind, I like that. Unfortunately I don\'t have any more Gabby Tongue in stock. I do have an Enchanted Fishing Rod for Snappers. How about you go and catch a Gabby Tongue yourself? By the way, I don\'t know if you knew but only some species of Snapper have one - orange, blue, white, green and Kloon, to be exact. If you don\'t catch one first time around, just keep trying and trying, these tongues can be hard to get a hold of. When you do finally get one you should go soak it in an enchanted well which you\'ll find below the enchanted lakes in the Koalak region. Remember to bring a climbing rope with you to get down there.";
D.q[5673] = "Gobball Horn? Just grab yourself a Gobball, I don\'t see what the problem is. What, you\'re not talking about that kind of horn? Listen, I\'d love to help you, but for starters you need to explain yourself more clearly, and secondly, I don\'t just give away information for free, if you know what I\'m saying.";
D.q[5678] = "So the information from that imbecile Divad was false. I\'m going to have a word with him. I don\'t like sending my warriors off on wild goose chases. As for you, go spread some unhappiness on your way and regain your status as a Knight of Despair.";
D.q[5710] = "Ok, I\'m going to explain the situation to you. I\'m your superior, so you\'d better not bother me unless you have a good reason.";
D.q[5789] = "Whenever I sneeze, time seems to take a turn for the worse. Rude people claim it\'s because I once tripped over that brown rug there and accidentally spilt Ouassingue Juice on the hands of Xelor\'s Clock, but that\'s not true - I\'m just allergic to pollen. I\'m doing my best to look after myself, but how am I supposed to stop myself from ever sneezing again?\nTo make up for all the trouble, I often hand out sweets to the long-suffering inhabitants of Amakna.\nThey seem to do the trick, and I\'m pretty proud of myself because at the moment, everything seems to be OK.\n\n*Rolls her eyes and sniffs noisily*\n\nOh no, oh...";
D.q[5794] = "So have you decided to help me catch the souls I need? Your quest will be long and perilous, but your reward will match your success. I\'ll give you a very powerful artefact, I\'ve little use for it myself. If you want to help me, go see my assistant, she\'ll tell you what souls I need and give you everything you need to catch them.";
D.q[6161] = "Since I created this creature and it escaped from me... I\'ve understood that I must find a way to conserve the essence of as many living creatures as I can. Something tells me that it will be useful in the future, and that great changes are approaching. The great story of natural evolution cannot end here, we cannot let it be swept away by a force we\'re not even sure exists... excuse me, I\'m rambling again...";
D.q[6173] = "Excellent, you\'ve made the right decision!\nGo quickly to Amayiro in the Bontarian Militia and tell him I sent you.\nActually, don\'t tell anyone else about this little favour as Astrubian militiamen aren\'t allowed to recruit on behalf of the big cities. It\'s our little secret, OK?";
D.q[6194] = "Let me siiiing, let me siiiii.... nnngggg.\nOh hello, I didn\'t hear you coming. So, tell me, doesn\'t that big boil in the middle of your face bother you? It\'s really horrible, you should try covering it up. \nBut what am I talking about... I forgot to introduce myself. My name is Pandalida, the famous singer from the first season of the Amakna\'s Got Talent. I hope you haven\'t come to get an autograph off me...";
D.q[6214] = "Since you\'re taking it like that, here\'s what I know - three clients have a name beginning with X. Xeloro Verpowered, Xephires and Xavier Norruck. Xeloro can often be seen around the handymen\'s quarter, but the others I\'ve no idea about.";
D.q[6219] = "If the Xephires you\'re talking about is indeed the one I\'m thinking or, well I know him very well. He comes here from time to time on business with other important people. The tailor Paro Cabanne could tell you more about it.";
D.q[6221] = "I won\'t be able to help. Xephires travels a lot. And now that you ask, I realise that I don\'t even know where he lives. Marge Gondersun the jeweller knows him well , she used to mind his children before she took over her mother\'s jewellers.";
D.q[6225] = "You seem nice, so I don\'t mind telling you a bit more, but keep it too yourself, ok...\nSo anyway, when I was babysitting Xephires\' kids, I often happened to overhear conversations about business... but I didn\'t always understand. Xephires had money trouble before, but within a few short months, all his problems had disappeared and he found himself in a comfortable position in Bontarian society. He sold his house for a bigger model and that\'s when I decided to take up the family business. \nHe has since changed house many times, but he sometimes calls round to visit and to make a few orders.";
D.q[6227] = "Hmph. An innkeeper is supposed to know everything about everything, is that it? What a bunch of losers... \nLucky for you, I did happen to find out a thing or two about Xephires. It might be useful. I\'ve a mission to give you involving Xephires. Guess what, one of your colleagues found a Sram who knows Xephires personally through some business deals in the past. But that idiot of a militiaman didn\'t bring the Sram back with him. I went a bit too hard on him and he wasn\'t able to get around so good anymore. So I need you to go find this Sram in the Treechnid forest and bring me back any information he might have.";
D.q[6228] = "I don\'t dare leave this grove, I can hear sounds and mocking laughter to the north of here. Could you go have a look and tell me if the path back is safe or not? I\'ll tell you anything you need to know if you do.";
D.q[6233] = "Hey, you there, get out of there!";
D.q[6235] = "The goblins attacked me by surprise while you were walking in the Treechnid forest. I killed a few but there were too many of them. Fortunately... I\'m a Sram, a skilful one at that, and after a few days\' march I managed to get away from them with a trick I\'m not going to tell you about right now. They followed me, and I ran until I hadn\'t a breath left in my body, and then hid on this ledge. But I can\'t get down again... could you help me? I\'d be so grateful.";
D.q[6236] = "I saw you had a climbing robe. Maybe with some friends, if everyone brought me one, we could make a monkey bridge. If everyone goes to the right place with a rope, attaching themselves to the tree, it should work out fine. Tell me when you\'re ready.";
D.q[6248] = "You\'re going to go to the goblin camp and bring this Sram. Just so you can say you haven\'t come for nothing, here are some potions that might be useful to you in case you get in trouble. If you find the adventure too risky, take some other militiamen with you, that\'ll give them some exercise and it\'ll mean I don\'t have to send them to get you as well as the Sram. Don\'t bother coming back without information, you know what\'ll happen to you if you do.";
D.q[6257] = "Could you get to him? Hahaha. It\'s impossible when there\'s no battle taking place - they\'re hiding in the Bonta militia building. All the same, they need as many Dragoturkeys as we do. I\'ll bet they buy their stock from Klako the famous Dragoturkey hunter.";
D.q[6260] = "Oto Mustam ordered the guard to be increased, and the Bontarians were overcome. They were handed over to Boud Chair to make tinned food. He also wants you to send a message to Captain Starky to say that his niece may suffer the same fate if he doesn\'t cooperate.";
D.q[6279] = "Listen carefully. You\'re MY dogsbody, not Milone\'s, you got it? It\'s up to me to say if your incompetence deserves to be punished. This time I\'m going to let you off. You\'ve lost enough time carrying out this plug\'s every desire.";
D.q[6282] = "What? Is it you who ruined my house with that horrible substance that stank out the countryside for miles around? Thanks to you, my plants died and my furniture has to be thrown out. So what exactly did you want?";
D.q[6283] = "I\'m sorry but I can\'t help you. Since I won the first season of Amakna\'s Got Talent, Pandalida has been constantly harassed as soon as she leaves her door. \nThe last time over enthusiastic admirers found out where she lived, they covered the walls with Tra Khben Paste and it took her a few weeks to get over it. After that she just had to move and it was then she became a regular here at my inn. It\'s an ill wind that blows well for no man, as they say.";
D.q[6284] = "You don\'t look like one of those crazy admirers, so I think I can make an exception in your case. It\'s easy, you\'ll see. Go out of Inn in the opposite direction to the sun\'s movement for half a league and then take the path which runs perpendicular to the Feudala-Akwadala axis which you plot at 90% to its original position for a quarter league. If you don\'t manage to find your way, just go to the south-west point of the port.";
D.q[6294] = "Hahahahaha. You\'re uglier than a Trool flea! Give me what you have and I\'ll let you live. Refuse and even your mother won\'t be able to recognise you when I\'m through.";
D.q[6299] = "I\'m going to get in touch with some lawless bandits east of Amakna. I\'ll enslave their souls and make unstraying footsoldiers of them. But to do this I need to capture their souls and find the objects required to perform the ritual.\nGo capture three dark baker souls, two dark miner souls and two dark smith souls. \nYou\'ll have to find a blue, a yellow and a green Corruptah Stone. Miners can create these stones from raw materials you\'ll get from alchemists. If they refuse to help you, don\'t hesitate to give them a whipping... or shove knackis up their nose, they\'re terrified of that for some reason.";
D.q[6318] = "At the beginning, I thought you were playing around, and then I said to myself that it wouldn\'t cost me anything to do the report. This equipment is totally useless and if it\'s not a joke of yours, well then whoever tries to use it won\'t have much luck.";
D.q[6319] = "I wouldn\'t usually say this but the smith who\'s supplying the militia is completely useless. The only reason he got the job is that his father does business with the attendant. It turns my stomach to think that this incompetent sod, Latem Sa, has been getting so much business. It\'s just another example of connections speaking louder than competence, and look what the result is. The smith should be in the smith workshop in Astrub... I didn\'t want him hanging around mine!";
D.q[6328] = "You\'re right, animals are much more intelligent than the inhabitants of this town. I love Bow Meows, they\'re so cute and their fur is as silky as mine. I used to travel all through Amakna with my Bow Meow training act until they were all confiscated and put in quarantine after eating Danathor the attendant\'s glistening Kido. Since then, I\'ve been training Whitish Fangs for the Bontarian Militia, trying to save up enough money to pay the fine for my Bow Meows.";
D.q[6331] = "I\'ve to tame Whitish Fangs for the Bontarian militia, I need the money to pay for my Bow Meows that Danathor the attendant put in quarantine. Luckily for me, I\'ll soon be coming into some Kamas.";
D.q[6340] = "What, what does it mean when... I see, you think you\'re smart don\'t you? Take this newly trained Whitish Fang and we\'ll see if Roy Sigfred\'s method is as effective as he says it is. I\'ll show you where the ambush happened. Hurry up and report back to me when you\'re done.";
D.q[6348] = "Well, that\'s not too bad. I\'ll be able to make my battle robots with this. You want to know what they do? Do you see me asking you any questions? Well, do you?";
D.q[6349] = "I knew it. You\'re only helping me to get what you want. That\'s not very charitable to be honest, it stinks of fish. I\'ve seen through your Machiavellian scheme... and since I\'m just about to test my Dragobutt I\'m going to have to ask you to leave!";
D.q[6355] = "The Panta Maria... It\'s been a while since I\'ve seen it in the Port of Madrestam. I\'m not sure if the Bontarian boat is due to pay a visit here anytime soon. Go ask the other inhabitants of the port, maybe they can fill you in. Come back to see me when you find out and let me know what they say, I\'ll stay here and keep my ear open too...";
D.q[6358] = "There\'s not a single piece of contraband merchandise that can pass through this port without me knowing about it. Why? Because I\'m the best at what I do and everyone in these parts fears me completely, even that old hag Wartella eats out of my hand if I want her to. She won\'t admit it, but it\'s true.";
D.q[6364] = "So nobody here could answer your questions? That means that The Panta Maria is not ready to dock. You should take a trip round Pandala, my friend Captain Banwana can help you - he knows what ships come in and out of the Port of Madrestam and Pandala, both legal and illegal. I could rent you a boat if you want to get there quicker, it\'ll only cost you 500 Kamas. You have to give me an answer right now.";
D.q[6369] = "Shush!\nThe horn we are talking about was part of a creature named Thelama who terrorised the distant province of Pandala.\nDuring an evening spent asking for the goddess\' help - some texts present this evening as a simple drinking session - the young Pandawushu disciple Fogornleg swore to his Master that he would defeat Thelama. Three months later, after Thelama had not been seen for five moons, Fogornleg\'s body was found, a bloody horn in his hand. Of Thelama there was no trace except the horn and so Fogornleg\'s Master gave it the name of his deceased disciple who had the courage to keep his promise at the cost of his life.\nThereafter, it became clear that the horn was vested with powerful magic which the Master Pandawa often use when they paid homage to the goddess. But what shouldn\'t have come to pass came to pass, and while recovering from an entire night spent praying to the goddess, the Horn was stolen.";
D.q[6371] = "Some slightly crazy adventurers have already set off looking for the Fogornleg Horn on Moon Island, and they claim to have seen the guardian. It\'s well worth noting that they were dressed up as Ambushers and had drunk a bottle of Greedoburg when he appeared to them, which says a lot for the credibility of their story. If I were you, I\'d take their advice with a large pinch of salt.";
D.q[6372] = "You really want to know how to prepare this rot-gut? Well, whatever you want, but don\'t come complaining if you have hallucinations or have a mad half hour after drinking too much.\nIf you plan to visit Moon Island, I\'d advise you to take a good fifty Kokonuts with you. It seems that you get stuck in the horrible Moon jungle without them. Brrr, it gives me goosebumps just thinking about it.";
D.q[6378] = "In fact, it happened a moment ago and I thank you on his behalf. You helped me so now it\'s my turn to help you.\nElturt is a very old, very wise turtle. He was thrown into the Amakna sewers when he was very young. After a time spent rubbing shoulders with Sphincter Cell and having defeated Herr Palp Itane in the Cania Marathon of 532 he was swept away by floodwaters during the great flood of 540 and beached on Wabbit Island, which at the time was inhabited by the Lenalds. Having failed to stem the Wabbit invasion, he swam all the way over to Moon Island. There, ashamed of his failure and being different from other turtles, he isolated himself in the deep jungle and has lived as a hermit until now.\nThey say he has strong powers inherited from his stay in the sewers and that he has sharpened his fighting techniques over the centuries. According to the latest rumours, he could be the guardian of a powerful magic horn but I didn\'t really pay much attention to them.";
D.q[6384] = "Eltuwt? That infewnal cweatuwe is still alive? What is this stowy you\'d have me believe? I don\'t want to heaw any mowe about him. He humiliated me and ovew the yeaws, I had to live in shame, and it\'s all his fault. Today, you\'we offewing me the oppowtunity to avenge myself and I find myself unable to help you. Why? Because I\'m widdled with awthwitis since the lightning stwuck my fingewtips. It\'s extwemely painful and debilitating. I can, howevew, tell you his weak spot, if you pwomise to avenge me.";
D.q[6391] = "To forge the tip of the back-scratcher you\'ll need a shovel smith to stand in front of the forge. They\'ll need to equip a Scratcher Smith Hammer, and have 2 Aluminite in their inventory, as well as 5 Iron and 1 Oilbow Grease.";
D.q[6403] = "It\'s been a long time since we made any of that kind of flour. It\'s for a funeral, I suppose? I\'m very sorry for your loss. Under the circumstances, I\'d be happy to give you the recipe. If you take the ingredients to a farmer, they should be able to make it for you - whatever their level.\nAnd don\'t worry, the soul of your former friend will end up reincarnated one day.";
D.q[6404] = "Where are the Kanis? Beware, the kani is treacherous, the kani is bad, the kani is big.\nAh, but I did not introduce myself. I\'m Sim the Soft, the greatest Kaniger hunter of all time. Believe it or not, I killed my first Kaniger at the age of 3. I then realised that by killing lots of those monsters, I was progressing faster than anyone. Yes, I understood that from a very young age and since then I\'ve progressed quickly, very quickly. I\'ve already killed 13,142,517 Kanigers and I\'m not about to stop anytime soon.";
D.q[6409] = "Now that is a tasty salad. Lots of meat, not much veg. It would be even better if you swapped the vegetables for more pieces of meat.\nYou want to know how to prepare it? I don\'t have a clue, I\'m afraid. Only certain adventurers who have mastered both butchery and hunting know the recipe. I remember a Cania hunter that used to eat it all the time, what was his name? Sam the Sif, Sim the Sweet...Sim the Soft! He often trains to the south of the Blop Dungeon, I\'ll mark the dungeon\'s location on your map for you. A little bit of meat for the road?";
D.q[6424] = "I\'m not the type to listen in on people\'s conversations. I heard the name by accident while they were talking about selling stolen goods.";
D.q[6435] = "Let\'s get things straight. I hung out with an Ecaflip for a while, until I realised that he was a loser. He claimed to be the head of a gang of bandits, so I asked him to show me where their hideout was. I wouldn\'t let up, and then finally he took me there. I had a look around and immediately realised he was far from the chief. He only took me there for his buddies\' sake. Ecaflips are a bunch of lame, blind-lucky one-armed bandits.";
D.q[6436] = "If it\'s to injure them I\'d love to help but don\'t think that we\'re friends, understand? You know where the Tainela Zaap is? Well it\'s nowhere near that! Give me that map, you\'re bloody useless.\nOnly Ecaflips from the gang are allowed in, so I hope we don\'t have too much trouble. The entrance is hidden behind a rock and it\'s useless to try gettin down without a rope - you\'d fall to your death! I advise you to go with a group, because these guys don\'t mess about. If they catch you, you\'ll know about it.";
D.q[6441] = "Thanks so much for your help . Those bandits were going to pillage our supplies before you and Brio came along. We owe you a debt of gratitude. When you return to Bonta, please come and see me. I\'ll reward you properly then...";
D.q[6456] = "I had some problems with an Ecaflip who matched your description. He had really bad manners and spent the whole night on my case. The innkeeper had to call the militia to get the guy out of there.\nYou want to know which militiaman? Wow, I really couldn\'t say. I don\'t know them all, but they were definitely accompanied by Captain Alrok. I remember because he came to ask if I was okay afterwards. If you want to find him, he\'ll be posted at the Bonta Zaap.";
D.q[6474] = "What did you think would happen? You\'re far too masculine for her. Look how blocky you are. You\'re more like a Bworkette than a Tanuki Chan.";
D.q[6480] = "The council spoke to him about a report criticising you and questioning your loyalty to Bonta. Ture Inge has a copy of the report, but he\'s asking for a Blo\'up Belt in exchange. He broke his own recently and he can\'t find a new one anywhere... to tell you the truth, he\'s probably just too cheap to pay the money!";
D.q[6487] = "Pretty much anyone can use this jelly. It\'s cheap to buy in the marketplace. I won\'t tell you the various uses it has - if I did you\'d probably never want to see any ever again!";
D.q[6488] = "Ah, it\'s you? I didn\'t recognize you with those ridiculous clothes on. Let\'s go quick, I really don\'t want anyone to notice us - and I definitely don\'t want to get put in chains here with so many Tofoones about.";
D.q[6491] = "Huhuhuheeheehee HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!\nI changed my mind and I wanted to give you the information for free, but since you insist... I\'ll take the sapphire.\nHuhuhuheeheehee HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!\nYou don\'t have access to the poison reserves, they\'re next to the Carvers\' Marketplace. Only people who have a natural talent for spying can get in there by taking out the hidden mechanisms that block the way in. On top of that, there are traps all over the place, and you\'ll need to have at least one person with you to open the grilles. Since you don\'t have any friends, I guess that means you\'re in trouble.\nHuhuhuheeheehee HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!";
D.q[6492] = "Hello hello. Are you a trader? No? Supplier? Trafficker? No? Hm, well I don\'t think I\'ve anything for you in that case. I organise convoys to Astrub.";
D.q[6504] = "Ok, so I\'ve got to go and guard the entrance to the Tower of Bonta? Ok, but if I don\'t get a bonus this time, I\'ll be really mad.";
D.q[6507] = "ahahahahahhaahahah\nHAHAHAHAHHARHARHARHHAA!\nGive me 1,000 Kamas and I\'ll tell you why I\'m laughing.\nGive me 1,500 Kamas and I\'ll tell you where the hidden gaming rooms are.\nHahahhahaaahahaaahaha\nHARHARHAHARHARHAAHA!";
D.q[6513] = "You mean you came especially for me? That\'s very nice, but I\'ve to work overtime. Since the boss died, I\'ve less time for myself. But that doesn\'t mean that it wouldn\'t have been a pleasure, quite the opposite, in fact! Another time, I promise.";
D.q[6516] = "You say that because I\'m a Sram, right? Srams for you are all the same, this is what you think, right? You\'re lucky that my 50 aren\'t here or you\'d end up as mincemeat. You\'re part of the militia as well? Well, it\'s no surprise that you\'re here to question me. I know nothing about Petra and even if I knew something I wouldn\'t tell you anything. You\'ll see what happens when my 50 arrive. Until then, you leave me alone, OK? I\'m making every effort to not break you in two you see... no, don\'t bother getting yourself wound up, I\'m just warning you. Okay, I\'ll shut up now, but you\'re lucky I know how to hold my nerve.";
D.q[6517] = "ahahahahahhaahahah\nHAHAHAHAHHARHARHARHHAA!\nYou look like someone who\'d appreciate the place, but when I\'m there I don\'t talk shop, so there\'s no point in keeping on asking. Come and play with us or find yourself another table.\nHahahhahaaahahaaahaha\nHARHARHAHARHARHAAHA!";
D.q[6526] = "I can\'t find my horn, and it\'s driving me up the wall. I\'m all wound up and I want to smash something. And what\'s more, that Ecaflip won\'t stop laughing and it\'s so very, very annoying! I\'ve a good mind to pull out his whiskers. That\'d soon shut him up.";
D.q[6532] = "Thank you for sparing me. I hope you enjoyed it and that the teeth marks on your body are not too painful.";
D.q[6539] = "To summarise: you took the money, you exploited the bitch to make her think she was saved and once you\'d had your wicked way with her, you killed her. I underestimated just how evil you were. To tell you the truth, it was just a test, a test you passed with flying colours! You actually killed Petra\'s double, while the real Petra was on her way here to give me a report of your actions. I\'m impressed. Continue like that, and you\'ll go far, I like my second fiddles to be like you. \nOne last point: don\'t even think about going near Petra again, for whatever reason! Have I made myself understood? If you so much as lay a finger on her, or even think about her, I\'ll force you to swallow a living Miremop.";
D.q[6548] = "I don\'t want to see you again until you bring me the bags I asked for. If you force the issue too much you\'ll end up in the depths of the giant Kralove\'s nose.\nI don\'t give a damn that it has no nose! Any other hole will do just as well.";
D.q[6552] = "Have you seen the militia\'s equipment, before you come here insulting me? This runt of an Osamodas got the entire contract! Can you believe that! Latem Sa is his name. He couldn\'t make so much as a saddle for a Tofu, never mind craft weaponry... You want to know what I think? His father got him the job, he\'s great friends with the attendant. Ah yes. If you want to find this incompetent fool, he\'ll be in Astrub, he\'s doing an apprenticeship there.";
D.q[6557] = "Competent smiths? I don\'t know many to be honest. There\'s me... and... let\'s see. There\'s another one called Hanniball Smisse. I used to work with him in the Bonta militia, but he deserted. He set up a forge in the village of Amakna, far from the terrible war.";
D.q[6559] = "I\'d have been fine with it if didn\'t already have a thousand late orders. I\'ve to forge weapons to slay the Moowolf, to scalp the Bworker and to gut the Minotot, so I really don\'t have time to equip the militia. I did know another smith a long time ago who mysteriously left for the mountains. I haven\'t seen him for ten years, so I\'m sure he for one won\'t be snowed under with work. Go see Graham Finame in the south-west workshop, he might remember where the mountain smith is.";
D.q[6560] = "My weapons are made to slay monsters and my armour, to protect from the same. I don\'t make equipment so men can slaughter each other. I knew a smith who was less scrupulous once, but he fled into the wild many years ago and nobody has seen him since. You don\'t know Norb, do you? That\'s the smith who recently set up shop on the Scaraleaf Plains.";
D.q[6569] = "Is Nara still alive? I always thought a Boowolf got the better of that old paranoid fool. If you want to know where to find a place for him, you\'ll have to give me something in exchange. Let\'s say 3,000 Kamas or an Enutrof\'s Memento.";
D.q[6576] = "I suppose you know what all this is about already, so I\'m not going to beat around the bush. Our militia is terrible, they can\'t coordinate themselves, and so our tactics are completely useless. We need to find a tactician who can form a link between our strategists and our brainless foot soldiers. \nThe Pandala Library is famous for its huge collection of works on military history, including the seminal Art of war in Getas, and War in Pieces. You\'ll definitely find someone who knows a thing or two about tactics over there.";
D.q[6584] = "The list? Ah yes, the list. Here you go. Get rid of this toolbox for me on your way there please, it\'s been taking up space in my forge for long enough.";
D.q[6588] = "I don\'t know any more about it, but I reckon the Sadidas hold a grudge against him still, even after all these centuries. If you really want to find out more, Epuop Tik at the Sadida Temple should be able to help you out. He\'s a living encyclopedia, he knows everything about everything that concerns his race. If you\'re really stuck, you can go see the Bwork Mages, but since they often hang out with their less evolved cousins, you\'ll probably have to smash a few heads in before you even start a conversation.";
D.q[6589] = "Blimey! Who told you about that? Were you worried about the spell on the trees? Well, let me tell you all about it. A few centuries ago, when belief in the gods was still weak, a most powerful, and most evil Bwork Mage from the caverns cast a terrible curse: Grafioze. The bewitchment was harmless to plants and animals with one exception, Elm trees. These majestic trees, which up to then had been so numerous, died in their hundreds from the bewitchment, and still the curse grew stronger. A group of Sadidas who were searching for the origin of the curse tracked the Bwork Mage to his lair and there they revisited one hundred fold the suffering he caused to the Elms. But Sadida himself found the punishment insufficient. He intervened in person and punished the Bwork in the worst way possible - he transformed him into a doll and gave him to the first mama Bwork he came across.";
D.q[6598] = "What have you done to that doll? Have you seen the state of it? It won\'t be easy to patch it up... I don\'t know if it\'s even possible. Well don\'t just stand there. Get me 1 Silkworm Cocoon, 1 Costumagus Needle, 5 Trunknid Leaves and 2 Black Gobbly Leathers.";
D.q[6603] = "I admire your skill, I understand why Amayiro thinks so much of you. Go back to him while we wait for the enchantment to take effect. Come back and see me when the doll is ready. Now that I think of it, take this purse of Kamas, everyone who is willing to serve the attendant is rewarded generously. If you continue to serve me well, you have every chance of climbing through the ranks of the militia, don\'t forget that. The Goddess Jiva appreciates women who are dedicated heart and body to the cause.";
D.q[6610] = "Hello, have you come with the Bwork Mage\'s spellbook?";
D.q[6612] = "That\'s the little Bontarian girl we gave a good spanking, isn\'t it?";
D.q[6707] = "Great, you really have a knack for getting out of sticky situations. Go see Liroye Merline, she might be able make copies of this key for you.";
D.q[6708] = "Let\'s go, everyone back to work.\n...\nI\'ve been told the Transgenesis is going to happen, so now we can get the rest of our crops growing at the same rate. Raymon Santho is gonna be happy. Speaking of old Ray, you should pay him a visit to find out how we\'re going to divvy up the crop. He\'s in Astrub at the moment, so you shouldn\'t have too much trouble finding him. He\'ll probably be around the Farmers\' Market wheeling and dealing as usual.";
D.q[6716] = "Ok, I\'ll leave this place and follow you to Bonta, but I\'ve to go and see Elya Wood first. She\'s a rich, beautiful Eniripsa, so I\'ll ask her to give us a few Kamas for equipment. Then I\'m going to ask her to marry me.";
D.q[6717] = "How dare you bring the most helpless, hopeless Eniripsa in the region to my temple. Nothing can cure him, he has no shame... he\'ll never learn to respect these things as long as he lives. On top of all that, he\'s unlucky. Get out of my sight.";
D.q[6719] = "I didn\'t think you\'d go so far, but if you continue, you\'ll start offending the other Dark Miners. If you\'ve nothing else to do here, I can take you back up to the top... just ask.";
D.q[6723] = "They didn\'t sent the best fighter in Bonta... next time try not to get a beatin\'. Wanna go back?";
D.q[6724] = "Oh, I\'m so very sorry. With the get up you have on, I thought you were fresh off the airship from Astrub. You really should have a word with your tailor.\nSo a Transgenesis spell was cast on my Oat crop? It\'s a good thing, mind you. It\'ll increase my production, so I\'ll earn more money. Tell Justfa Lafs that I\'ll pass by to talk to him and Danathor the attendant about how we\'re going to use it to feed the militia.";
D.q[6726] = "And there you have it. Take that to your boss and show him who\'s the very best smith in Amakna.";
D.q[6732] = "You\'re back? So you still haven\'t done anything about that horrible thing on your face. I know an excellent amateur surgeon, he used to be a butcher, but the steaks he\'d cut were far too small for peoples\' liking. He has to make a living after all, right? What\'s his name again?";
D.q[6753] = "I thought he\'d beat you - and I wasn\'t wrong, was I... It\'s a good thing the guards you posted at the bottom of the tower cut down them down while they were escaping. \nYour help and determination have been very valuable all the same. Bonta owes you a great debt for having revealed the identity of this traitor. Him and his accomplice will be thoroughly questioned and I\'ll make sure that Xephires\' riches are shared out among all our people.";
D.q[6755] = "There are four types. Resistant Gobtubbys who can take the fiercest of attacks.\nThe second, devoted Pandawa cubs, can heal wounds. Then there are the Dragoones who can overcome their enemies from a distance. \nFinally you have agile Bow Meows who excel in close combat with their steely claws. Which type do you think would suit you?";
D.q[6759] = "The most dangerous are still the Bwork Mages of the caverns, a rare type of Bwork which is, bless goddess Feca, on the point of extinction. We also owe the destruction of nearly all the Elms in the World of Twelve to a Bwork Mage who cast a curse called the Grafioze...";
D.q[6760] = "Hey zere. I\'z really happy to zee you guys, you \'ave changed my life. Sanks to you I won\'t \'ave to leave my village... I\'m eternally grateful. What brings you \'ere anyway?";
D.q[6761] = "Four Zadidas are needed to carry out ze rituel... four experienced Zadidas, zat is. Ze best way to know if zey are good iz to get zem to summon an Inflatable. Ze best place is in ze souzern part of ze enchanted lakes. Ze norss is too near ze Forest of ze Dark Treechnids.";
D.q[6765] = "What are you doing here? The god Sadida forbids all creatures but his disciples to come this way, and even they need a good reason, if they don\'t wish to anger him. I saw Sadida when he was angry once, and I don\'t want to see it again, and I was only watching... imagine what it was like for the poor souls who annoyed him. It was terrible, I\'ve trouble even thinking of it. I don\'t want to experience it again, so I advise you to leave this place right now. Of course you can try and convince me that you can\'t go back because Sadida\'s magic won\'t let you out of here... well if that\'s true, how did you get here in the first place? I didn\'t see any road signs... maybe you just followed your nose!";
D.q[6766] = "I see you coming, I\'m not stupid like a sacrificial doll, nor am I crazy, like a Madoll. What I\'m is a unique creation of the god Sadida, and several decades after he brought me to life, he gave me the enormous responsibility of watching over this place and guarding it against invaders from a distance. He knew that by giving me this task, he might not ever see me again. It was a huge sacrifice for him to have made. He must have cried for years when I left and to be honest, I don\'t think he\'ll ever be the same. It doesn\'t surprise me, he really enjoyed my company, you know. What a sad story.";
D.q[6770] = "I don\'t look after that any more. I played dice for the rank of attack commander with Rekojel and I lost. Why would I bet against an Enutrof, you ask? If Oto Mustam finds out, I\'ll be thrown in prison or worse, forced to infiltrate the Bonta militia. I\'d rather die than be surrounded by those sissies!";
D.q[6771] = "HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!\nDid that idiot Kapp Tenn tell you how he lost the commandment?\nHOHOHOHOHO!\nIf there\'s anything else you want to know, you\'ll have to go to the checkout!\nHIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!";
D.q[6772] = "HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!\nI sold the commandment to Shush Tercesasti. Remember him, he\'s the master of the Order of the Putrid Eye. I also heard that the plan has changed, and the new one is with Shush Tercesasti\'s documents. You\'ll have a hard time going to fetch them, if that\'s what you\'re planning.\nHIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!";
D.q[6779] = "Haha, I can imagine what\'ll happen already... when the Dragoturkeys release their gases, and the gases meet with Brakmar\'s sulphurous air, we\'ll have the first fully organic fireworks display in history! I only feel sorry for the poor mounts... if the gas drops in pressure at all, they\'ll be in trouble!";
D.q[6782] = "Quiet down, not everyone here wants to know about your personal life. I know a few remedies to the misfortunes this Bwork mage is going through, but they\'re very difficult to carry out. Do you really want to know what they\'re?";
D.q[6784] = "HIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!\nOnce I made Shush Tercesasti Jump with fright while he was having an allergy attack and talking to Malicia Misery, the owner of the inn of the same name. Maybe that nugget of information will help you!\nHIARHIARHIARHAHAHA!";
D.q[6813] = "If you\'re asking me it means that you\'ve already gone to see Sabine in her cell..? What do you mean no? Get going, quick or I\'ll put on my big boots and kick your butt.";
D.q[6896] = "Hahaha, she\'s a frisky one alright. But you know, not all Iops are idiotic headbangers. Take Helsephine for example. A disciple of Iop and a successful alchemist at once. Ok, I mean, she was only a woman after all, but apart from that she wasn\'t too bad. \nMen usually like nothing much besides the blood and sweat of the battlefield, but there too you find exceptions. Rish Claymore, now there\'s a cultured fellow. He might have got where he\'s through violence, but since he arrived, he\'s taken up cooking, sewing and tennis, among other refined pastimes. A shining example of Iopness.";
D.q[7049] = "I classed the gems according to the monsters they contain. Which one do you want?";
D.q[7071] = "At the very end of this cave, my father and his followers do live. What I\'d really like is if you could get all the way to him. If he\'s had an accident, I\'ll take his place. I never told you that, of course!";
D.q[7136] = "You\'ve got guts, I can see that. You\'ll need them. Go fight the Dopples in the temples of the gods. If you come out on top, the master of each Dopple you beat will reward you well. Do you want to start right away?";
D.q[7469] = "This power allows you to reset your characteristics to 101, if you don\'t want to lose anything you\'ve gained through scrolls.\nIf you use it, any characteristic above the value 101 will be reset to 101, and you\'ll get back the appropriate number of characteristic points. A characteristic below the value 101 will not be affected.\nDo you really want to continue?";
D.q[7557] = "You were fast. That\'s good, because your job is to take a package to the village of Akwadala as soon as possible. I want you to go there to deliver a crate to Pandette, he will pay you after receiving the package.";
D.q[7558] = "You\'re not to look inside this crate, its contents are of no interest to you. Just be happy delivering it to the right person and you\'ll be paid for your efforts.";
D.q[7561] = "If you want my opinion, you\'ve got yourself mixed up in something really dodgy there, but we might be able to take advantage of the situation.\nHave you got the list with you?";
D.q[7568] = "I\'ll give this antidote to Grandapan right away. If it works, the Pandawas will owe you a debt of gratitude.\nAs for the unscrupulous merchants who used the Ouassingue juice, they will be punished as is necessary.\nSince you\'ve worked so well for our cause, why don\'t you visit Pandala Island? The assistant Shaman is a good friend of mine, he will help you get your bearings.";
D.q[7575] = "Which city would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[7576] = "Where else would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[7580] = "What?! You\'ve lost my scalpel? That was a high precision tool, a jewel in the crown of modern surgery. Ugh. Well, anyway, I should really give you another one if I want to create a companion. It\'ll cost you 1,000 Kamas.";
D.q[7593] = "Looks like I have a guest. \nI can see your eyes shining with lust. You\'re wondering how a slob like yourself could earn even a hundredth of my wealth. \nHahaha, well, dream on, buddy. Never going to happen.";
D.q[7598] = "That was an excellent fight, you fully deserve your reward. \nCome and see me again soon, maybe I\'ll be inclined to let you fight another one of my hunting trophies.";
D.q[7604] = "Imagine, if you will, the heinous crime that these awful - no, worse than that - atrocious monsters have committed.\nThose fiends broke into Father Kwismas\' workshop and cleared it out before returning to the depths of their dungeon.\nUnless someone does something to stop them, the children of the World of Twelve will not be able to celebrate Kwismas this year.\nDo you understand what that means?";
D.q[7605] = "Oh, I\'m glad you\'re taking it that way.\nYou can help by retrieving one of the boxes of presents stolen by those terrible fiends. Apparently, despite their abhorrent, unrepentant, soulless behaviour, they can be made to feel some remorse for their actions if Father Kwismas himself talks to them and asks for the stolen boxes to be returned. Perhaps you should try to pass yourself off as him, and if the thieves still aren\'t convinced, a good blow to the head should sort them out.";
D.q[7613] = "I can\'t help you unless you have a Bunch of Keys. To get one, head over to your class temple. You\'ll win a doploon if you\'re able to defeat a Dopple in the temple, and you can exchange it for a Bunch of Keys, which will give you free access to all of the dungeons in the game once a week.";
D.q[7616] = "Long ago, even before the creation of Xelor\'s Clock, Crocabulia displeased her master, the god Osamodas. Given a last chance to redeem herself, Crocabulia agreed to watch over a young and fragile new race: the dragons.\nTo ensure that she carried out her mission, Osamodas entombed the formidable Grozilla and Grasmera in the Sanctuary.\nTheir first awakening, caused by human folly, was terrible, and heralded the destruction of Amakna\'s founding village. After the massacre, they returned to the bowels of the earth, hidden away in the Sanctuary. The legends told nothing more of them.";
D.q[7619] = "Show me what you\'ve got there.\nWhy, it\'s a Sauroshell fragment!\nIf you\'d like, you can give it to me, and I\'ll give you a magic amulet in return. Not just any amulet, mind - this amulet will show everyone that you were here when the battle took place.";
D.q[7620] = "But... that giant fang that you\'ve got there comes from the jaw of one of the two dragons, doesn\'t it?\nIt\'s enormous! I\'ve never seen one as big. It must make people jealous...\nIf you like, you can give it to me. I\'ll give you a shield fashioned from one of Grozilla\'s scales in return, so that everyone will see how mighty your deeds were.";
